0"><ph name="&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph1959151418587&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;" word-end="false">&lt;ph id="f0"&gt;</ph><props><value key="prefix"></value><value key="localName">ph</value><value key="namespaces"></value><value key="isEmptyElement">False</value><value key="nodeType">Element</value><value key="displayText">&lt;ph class="- topic/ph " conref="en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595" id="ph1959151418587" idp:conrefpath="200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009" idp:userph="true"/&gt;</value><value key="hasDisplayText">True</value><value key="attribute:id">f0</value></props></tag><tag id="1"><ph name="&lt;ph class=&quot;- topic/ph &quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595&quot; id=&quot;ph16288346152013&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009&quot; idp:userph=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;" word-end="false">&lt;ph id="f0"&gt;</ph><props><value key="prefix"></value><value key="localName">ph</value><value key="namespaces"></value><value key="isEmptyElement">False</value><value key="nodeType">Element</value><value key="displayText">&lt;ph class="- topic/ph " conref="en-us_topic_0000001645659009.xml#ph122067484595" id="ph16288346152013" idp:conrefpath="200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000001596019118#EN-US_TOPIC_0000001645659009" idp:userph="true"/&gt;</value><value key="hasDisplayText">True</value><value key="attribute:id">f0</value></props></tag></tag-defs></header><body><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ac184932-032f-4ef8-8d30-48010c299342"><source>Why Does the Battery Charge and Discharge at the Same Electricity Price?</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="1">Why Does the Battery Charge and Discharge at the Same Electricity Price?</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="1">Waarom laadt de batterij op en ontlaadt hij bij dezelfde elektriciteitsprijs?</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="1"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">KCKPYcMav4zQ3CaVUKaDRsWtjs4=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="140c79b0-1f67-4450-bea8-43a5e4027592"><source>Intelligent scheduling policy (economic optimization)</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="2">Intelligent scheduling policy (economic optimization)</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="2">Intelligent planningsbeleid (economische optimalisatie)</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="2"><sdl:rep id="qcdCUbtcmuNagBeabFy/xQTJ8Xc=" /><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">qcdCUbtcmuNagBeabFy/xQTJ8Xc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="bce11040-92e1-4078-8dcd-22a2a2afabaa"><source>The <x id="0" /> uses AI algorithms to forecast future PV output, load demand, and grid status.</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="3">The <x id="0" /> uses AI algorithms to forecast future PV output, load demand, and grid status.</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="3">De <x id="0" /> gebruikt AI-algoritmen om toekomstige PV-opbrengst, belastingsvraag en netstatus te voorspellen.</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="3"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">WdygCJ5YbMqLK5nCgnpWYrxfCVA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d021444e-9e2b-47b3-bf6c-af7961d08a90"><source>If a sharp increase in load or a sudden decrease in PV output is forecast, the system will charge in advance to build up a power reserve, even if electricity prices remain the same, to cope with short-term power deficits.</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="4">If a sharp increase in load or a sudden decrease in PV output is forecast, the system will charge in advance to build up a power reserve, even if electricity prices remain the same, to cope with short-term power deficits.</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="4">Als een sterke toename van de belasting of een plotselinge afname van de PV-opbrengst wordt voorspeld, zal het systeem van tevoren opladen om een energiereserve op te bouwen, zelfs als de elektriciteitsprijzen gelijk blijven, om kortetermijntekorten aan stroom op te vangen.</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="4"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">TIN0/TmmAc1Cm/LBp04C8Va1nyE=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="ba19277f-e162-4898-a8dc-6557429451bb"><source>For example, when the system forecasts that high-power appliances (such as an air conditioner or electric water heater) will be turned on in the home one hour later and PV output may be insufficient at that time, it will charge from the grid in advance to ensure sufficient energy to cope with the peak load.</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="5">For example, when the system forecasts that high-power appliances (such as an air conditioner or electric water heater) will be turned on in the home one hour later and PV output may be insufficient at that time, it will charge from the grid in advance to ensure sufficient energy to cope with the peak load.</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="5">Wanneer het systeem bijvoorbeeld voorspelt dat over een uur in de woning energie-intensieve apparaten (zoals een airconditioner of elektrische boiler) worden ingeschakeld en dat de PV-opbrengst op dat moment onvoldoende kan zijn, zal het systeem van tevoren vanaf het net opladen om voldoende energie te hebben om de piekbelasting op te vangen.</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="5"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">o12S0ysdurXKhq8+cEpGSOUuCl0=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="d0b8171f-88ef-4a2e-92f1-5542d5a76a7f"><source>Inter-period policy linkage</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="6">Inter-period policy linkage</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="6">Koppeling van beleid tussen perioden</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="6"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">qrRV/0XUoKPmzrj1tiFpDWSu4jc=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="438028f0-e5e5-432b-ba15-0d15b7f31a1d"><source>The <x id="1" /> comprehensively considers electricity prices and loads over a longer time horizon.</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="7">The <x id="1" /> comprehensively considers electricity prices and loads over a longer time horizon.</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="7">De <x id="1" /> houdt op uitgebreide wijze rekening met elektriciteitsprijzen en belastingen over een langere tijdshorizon.</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="7"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">i22nxEKo2x5/r67KcjpvW0UK/nk=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group><group><sdl:cxts><sdl:cxt id="1" /><sdl:cxt id="2" /><sdl:cxt id="3" /></sdl:cxts><trans-unit id="faf8e549-1d33-4bf7-8b77-7d9661f5dde7"><source>If the system forecasts that the electricity price peak will be higher the next day, it may choose to charge during the current same-price period and reserve energy for a discharge opportunity with higher returns the next day, rather than discharging fully right away.</source><seg-source><mrk mtype="seg" mid="8">If the system forecasts that the electricity price peak will be higher the next day, it may choose to charge during the current same-price period and reserve energy for a discharge opportunity with higher returns the next day, rather than discharging fully right away.</mrk></seg-source><target><mrk mtype="seg" mid="8">Als het systeem voorspelt dat de elektriciteitsprijs-piek de volgende dag hoger zal zijn, kan het ervoor kiezen om op te laden tijdens de huidige periode met dezelfde prijs en energie te reserveren voor een ontlaadmogelijkheid met hogere opbrengst de volgende dag, in plaats van onmiddellijk volledig te ontladen.</mrk></target><sdl:seg-defs><sdl:seg id="8"><sdl:value key="SegmentIdentityHash">V+BOASwdeLs5dJqpYx3kR1q2NRA=</sdl:value></sdl:seg></sdl:seg-defs></trans-unit></group></body></file></xliff>